<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="84" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Male holotype</emphasis>
: (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18A-C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A male habitus, dorsal (SMF) B female habitus, dorsal (SMF). Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646999" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">19A</figureCitation>
). Total length: 7.4; carapace: 4.6 long, 3.2 wide.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646999" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" start="Figure 19" startId="F19">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Figure 19.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Crespo" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Hogna" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hogna isambertoi" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isambertoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Hogna isambertoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">A</emphasis>
male habitus, dorsal (SMF) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">B</emphasis>
female habitus, dorsal (SMF). Scale bars: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Colour</emphasis>
: carapace greyish brown, covered with short black setae, with a median yellow longitudinal band, anteriorly broadened, covered with short white setae; two yellow marginal bands, suffused with grey patches, covered with short white setae; four black striae well visible on each flank. Chelicerae yellow, with grey suffused patches, covered in black and white setae. Gnathocoxae and labium overall pale yellow, with posterior margin with suffused grey patch; sternum pale yellow, with V-shaped grey patch. Legs pale yellow, with irregular grey suffused patches, except anterior metatarsi and tarsi, yellowish orange. Pedipalps yellow. Abdomen with a pair of anterolateral black patches, extending laterally into grey to black flanks; a median faint dark lanceolate patch is bordered by two yellowish longitudinal bands interconnected in anterior half, posteriorly by means of dark chevrons; venter yellowish, with large blackish patches near spinnerets and small patches medially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Eyes</emphasis>
: MOQ: MW = 0.8 PW, MW = 1.1 LMP, MW = 1.1 AW; Cl = 0.5 DAME. Anterior eye row slightly procurved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Legs</emphasis>
: Measurements: Leg I: 11.7, TiI: 2.6; Leg IV: 13.8, TiIV: 2.8; TiIL/D: 6.6. Spination of Leg I: FeI: d1.1.1, p0.0.1; TiI: p1.0.1, v2l.2l.2s; MtI: p0.0.1, r0.0.1, v2l.2l.1s. MtI with sparse scopulae in basal half and dense scopulae on distal half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Pedipalp</emphasis>
: cymbium with one spine along prolateral rim and five dark, stout, macrosetae at tip, Fe with two dorsal and an apical row of four spines. Tegular apophysis with ventral spur very short, blunt, with a concave ridge leading to a thin apical point (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18A, B</figureCitation>
); terminal apophysis in close apposition with subterminal apophysis, which is blade-shaped with blunt end (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18A, C</figureCitation>
); embolus long and thick, with tip tilted anteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18A</figureCitation>
); palea large (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Hogna isambertoi sp. nov. A-C male (SMF): A left male palp, ventral B detail of the median apophysis, anteroventral C SEM image, right male palp, ventral D, E female (SMF): D epigynum, ventral E vulva, dorsal. Abbreviations, male palp: C - cymbium, E - embolus, MA - median apophysis, P - palea, T - tegulum, TA - terminal apophysis. Abbreviations, female genitalia: D - diverticulum, H - epigynal hoods, MS - median septum, S - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A); 0.2 mm (B-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1086.68015.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/646998" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">18A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Female paratype</emphasis>
: (Figs 
