<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="84" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="84">the species seems to be restricted to a very small area, equivalent to an Extent of Occurrence and Area of Occupancy of 8 km2 in two locations, both threatened by the effects of increasing aridification. The trends are unknown, but it is uncertain if the scarcity of specimens is due to rarity, or the fact that it seems to be a late autumn / early winter species, when collecting effort has been low. If the decline is confirmed the status might be Endangered, if not it might be Near Threatened.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
